<br>
Serious. <p><HR Width="25%" Align="Left">
<Font Size="2">
Sage Eelyen of the Nexus<BR>
<a href="http://www.anthologyguild.com" style="text-decoration: none; color: #4c6e9e">Guildleader of Anthology</a><BR>
</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=uuenavanlight>Uuena Van Light</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 195<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/5/03 8:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Behemoth</span><hr size=1> Make sure you have lots of Bards and/or Enchanters!!!!<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=arkein>Arkein</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/5/03 7:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Behemoth</span><hr size=1> Keep spiders outta room and ZERG!! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=enoah35>Enoah35</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 715<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/15/03 5:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Behemoth</span><hr size=1> Some info...<br>
<br>
It takes considerable amount of time till he become targettable. The keeper group must keep the spiders away from behemoth room or you will have a 4k AE bombarding in the room which = death. <br>
<br>
Behemoth himself has less than 100k hp, or around that range. He does not hit that hard eighther. What makes him hell are his ae spells. He has 3 types of nasty aes:<br>
<br>
900ish per tick Dot with initial damage ( forgot how much ) this is cold based. Liquid something it was called and can be resisted.<br>
<br>
400 or 700 damage with knockback effect... i think... forgot the name.<br>
<br>
Silence. But this has very short range. about 100? Can be avoided but its unresistable.<br>
<br>
Zerging this guy can be an option but not recomended. The fight cannot be more than 1 - 2 min since if it stays up that much, almost all the time 80% of the people would be dead via dot + AE. Keeper group is very important too since if behemoth moves and any spider gets in all caster healer would probably be ripped to shreds. heard the case that there is a high chance of wiping in enrage since he has very very low hp no one can would'nt even notice. <br>
<br>
IMHO, burst power is the key. We did him twice and failed twice, 1st try was because of the position of the behemoth and we haven't even used ae elixir ( it helps much ), 2nd try we downed to 30% but lack of damage and heals wiped us.<br>
<br>
This is about it... he is not that hard if you can find a reasonable tactics. Oh and CCH rotation is NOT necesary but rather Super Remedy spam. 1 - 2min fight also means that if you don't kill in that range most likely clerics would run out of mana too...<br>
<br>
Enoah <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=arkein>Arkein</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/15/03 9:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Behemoth</span><hr size=1> The 3 times we took him down, fight last for only 45sec to 1min max. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=delfontes>Delfontes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 150<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/23/03 1:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Behemoth</span><hr size=1> Anyone have a lucy link for the silence he casts?<br>
<br>
I'm thinking the range is pretty short, 50 or so, and a very short duration... but can't seem to find it.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nuken>Nuken</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/03 3:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Behemoth</span><hr size=1> can this guy be hit by reg. nukes or do u have to use lures? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gremer>Gremer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/9/03 11:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Behemoth</span><hr size=1> Regular nukes hit just fine. <p>Gremer&lt;BR&gt;<br>
Sorcerer of Erollisi Marr&lt;BR&gt;<br>
Proud Member of Affliction</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=delfontes>Delfontes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 199<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/9/03 12:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> Depends on what you mean by 'regular nuke'.<br>
<br>
I've seen ISOS bounce off him, or be partially resisted.<br>
<br>
Pop lvl 62+ draughts seem to be fine, because of the -50 to resist adjuster, and the fact that you are lvl 62+.<br>
<br>
61 or under, lures will be the only thing you consistantly land...<br>
<br>
Keep in mind that the fight is FAST, 1 resist and your DPS for the fight would have been better using lures.  You wont be going OOM <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=velhopaukkusmurffi>Velho Paukkusmurffi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/11/03 3:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> 4 groups, one in each spider corner<br>
<br>
mt in room once spiders stopped<br>
<br>
use runed rogues to charge him and disc at certain point<br>
<br>
wizards will nuke hard from out of ae range (best imo as mentioned earlier are pop draughts and tears of arlyxir)<br>
<br>
clerics should use sup remedy spam to gain more range than the limited CH range of 100<br>
<br>
So only ones really getting hit by the nasty AEs will be the MT, maybe backup tank if need and rogues. <p>Velho<br>
Arcanist of The Celestial Rapture<br>
Kane Bayle<br>
